OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJack Ritchie inquest:      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FGambling addict help       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F'woefully inadequate'      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A teacher with a gambling addiction who
OL,6, took his own life was failed by        
OL,7, "woefully inadequate" warnings and     
OL,8, treatments, a coroner has said.        
OL,10,FJack Ritchie's disorder had "spiralled 
OL,11,Fout of control" before his death aged  
OL,12,F24, but the help available did not meet
OL,13,Fhis needs, an inquest heard.           
OL,15,FThe resulting "feelings of shame and   
OL,16,Fhopelessness" had made him feel        
OL,17,Fsuicidal, coroner David Urpeth said.   
OL,19,FMr Ritchie's parents said gambling was 
OL,20,F"the root and trigger of Jack's death".
